		<description><![CDATA[Sorry guys, yes I am saying sorry been so busy the past week that I have not been able to update my details for you guys. &#160; Night Rating: &#160; Since my last posting I let you guys know of my night adventure over Gauteng and being able to see [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Sorry guys, yes I am saying sorry been so busy the past week that I have not been able to update my details for you guys.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Night Rating:</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Since my last posting I let you guys know of my night adventure over Gauteng and being able to see the night skies, the bustling cars on the streets below, and the city lights mapping its way over the scenery. This was the last step on my way to getting my rating, I did my prep test on the Tuesday where we spent nearly two hours in the General flying area practicing steep turns, descending turns, limited panel, unusual attitudes all with those evil <a href="http://www.jaybird.co.za/?p=328">foggles</a> I told you about in the very beginning.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Then the test came and we pretty much did everything that I did in the test prep and passed with flying colours, I am now rated to fly at night and give you guys pictures to everything I see from the air. What took me nearly 5 months, of which not all the time waiting was my fault, R30 000 +-, and nearly 20 odd hours I can officially have my piece of paper printed saying Night Rating as seen below:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span id="more-512"></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.jaybird.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/P5170300.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-520" title="Night Rating " src="http://www.jaybird.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/P5170300.jpg" alt="Night Rating " width="1737" height="2316" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2></h2>
<h2>Swartkop Airshow 2012</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Apart from just doing my Night Rating I also had the chance to head to the Airshow at Swartkop Airforce Base in Centurion, I did not take many pics because I actually wanted to watch this airshow and all the pretty planes, if you want to see more of the pics check them out <a href="http://www.avcom.co.za/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?f=15&amp;t=34946&amp;p=1072424&amp;hilit=swartkop#p1072424">here</a> and details of the airshow <a href="http://www.avcom.co.za/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?f=12&amp;t=93971&amp;hilit=swartkop&amp;start=75">here</a>. The list of planes that were at the show are below, with provision for some that did not fly on the day due to certain circumstances.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The civilian participating aircraft on the day include of the following:<br />
1. 13 X Alloutte II<br />
2. 2 X Alloutte III<br />
3. 1 x Bell 47<br />
4. 2 x Austers<br />
5. 8 x Bosboks<br />
6. 1 x DC3<br />
7. 3 x Kudus<br />
8. 1 x Chipmunk<br />
9. 14 x Harvards<br />
10. 1 x Cessna 17<br />
11. 7 x Tiger Moths<br />
12. 1 x Stumpe U<br />
13. 2 x T-28s<br />
14. 3 x Albatross<br />
15. 2 x Extra 300s<br />
16. 6 x Yak 52s<br />
17. 3 x L-39s<br />
18. 1 x L-29s<br />
19. 1 x T2 Buckeye<br />
20. 1 x Impala<br />
21. 1 x Cheetah<br />
22. 2 x Vampires<br />
23. 1 x Hunter<br />
24. Scully Levine &#8211; Gabriel Pitts Special team<br />
25. Arnie Meneghelli &#8211; Eqstra Harvard team<br />
26. Dennis Spence Goodyear Pitts Special team<br />
27. Brad Bennetts Mazda Zoom Zoom team.</p>
<p>From African Pilot Newsletter<br />
SAAF participating aircraft include the following:</p>
<p>1. 1 x Gripen<br />
2. 2 x Hawks<br />
3. 2 x Oryx helicopters<br />
4. 1 x Rooivalk helicopter<br />
5. 2 x Cessna Caravans<br />
6. 1 x Casa 212<br />
7. 1 x Dakota C47TP.<br />
8. 6 Astra (Silver Falcons)<br />
9. 1 x Hercules C-130</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
